This paper deals with natural language processing and semantic parsing, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). It also involves machine learning techniques for processing and transforming syntactic dependencies, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve training and evaluating models, which is a common task in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of logical forms and the focus on multilingual applications suggest a potential connection to natural language generation (cs.NE). Finally, the use of question answering and Freebase suggests a potential connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
